\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 06, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ure1665702745274.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ure1665702745274.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ure1665702745274.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ure1665702745274\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ure1665702745274__support_for_distributed_applications_99718\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Uniface applications are normally distributed over networked computers, with components, data, and resources located and communicating with each other by means of various types of middleware.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ure1665702745274__topic_d20347e1_d20348e1_d20349e1_d20350e1_d20351e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d893056e57\">Content Overview</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ure1665702745274__p_d30590e1_d30591e1_d30592e1\">The information in this collection describes the servers, connectors, and features that enable Uniface applications to be distributed over a network.</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ure1665702745274__table_d3161e1_d3162e1_d3163e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Uniface Servers <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15533e1_d15534e1_d15535e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pnt1665702745346.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pnt1665702745346.html\" title=\"Uniface middleware consists of various tools and processes that allow a distributed, heterogeneous collection of objects to work together over a network. The Uniface Router and Uniface Servers provide the basis for client applications (whether desktop, mobile, or web) to call in to the Uniface server architecture, and to call out to other technologies such as SOAP web services, RESTful web services, other URLs, or mail services.\">Uniface Application Middleware</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15536e1_d15537e1_d15538e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"upi1665702529312.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/upi1665702529312.html\" title=\"A Uniface Server is a server-based process that handles requests for remote data and component execution that it receives from client applications.\">Uniface Server</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15539e1_d15540e1_d15541e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"exm1665702529212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/exm1665702529212.html\" title=\"The Uniface Router is a multi-threaded process (urouter) responsible for interprocess communication in Uniface applications. It listens for requests from Uniface client applications and routes them to the appropriate Uniface Server, and it passes messages between various Uniface applications.\">Uniface Router</a>\n</li>\n</ul></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Network Support <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15542e1_d15543e1_d15544e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ilh1665702745499.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ilh1665702745499.html\" title=\"Uniface supports TCP/IP for basic network communication and TLS/SSL for secure communication over a network or the internet. Each Uniface installation includes network connectors for both protocols, and you can configure the connections between clients and servers to use either connector, depending on your security requirements.\">Network Support</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15545e1_d15546e1_d15547e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"obb1665702544994.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/obb1665702544994.html\" title=\"The TCP connector provides network connectivity via the TCP/IP protocol. It handles unsecured IPv4 and IPv6 connections. It also establishes the physical connection for secure communication using the TLS connector.\">TCP Connector</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15548e1_d15549e1_d15550e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mow1665702545090.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mow1665702545090.html\" title=\"The TLS network connector provides an encrypted network connection between the Uniface Router and its Uniface Servers and client applications. It can also be used by the UPOPMAIL component to connect to SMTP servers over TLS.\">TLS Connector</a>\n</li>\n</ul></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Asynchronous Messaging <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15551e1_d15552e1_d15553e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"mal1665702690837.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mal1665702690837.html\" title=\"To communicate with each other asynchronously, Uniface components can send asynchronous messages (often known as postmessages). Components can send messages to other components running in the same Uniface client process, in other client processes, and in shared Uniface Server processes. Messages sent between different processes are transported via the Uniface Router.\">Asynchronous Messaging</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15554e1_d15555e1_d15556e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"uyo1665702691073.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/uyo1665702691073.html\" title=\"The Message API Utility sends messages to a Uniface application from a non-Uniface Windows application using Uniface's remote postmessage mechanism.\">Message API Utility</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15557e1_d15558e1_d15559e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wtd1665702577667.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wtd1665702577667.html\" title=\"Send a message from one component instance to another.\">postmessage</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15560e1_d15561e1_d15562e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ioh1665702690765.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ioh1665702690765.html\" title=\"UTIMER is an internal Uniface component that sets a timer that can post messages to a specified component instance as a notification that a specified time period has elapsed. It can be used, for example, to check status or to poll a database at regular intervals.\">UTIMER</a>\n</li>\n</ul></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Database Support <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15563e1_d15564e1_d15565e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sha1665702562347.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sha1665702562347.html\" title=\"Uniface enables applications to connect to a wide variety of data sources, including relational databases, files, or directory servers. For example, an application could connect to an Oracle database, files on a server, and an LDAP server. Database connectors provide the interface between Uniface and specific databases\">DBMS Support</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15566e1_d15567e1_d15568e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lsp1665702531534.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lsp1665702531534.html\" title=\"To access, retrieve, and store data, Uniface provides database connectors that translate Uniface I/O requests into the target database's data definition and manipulation languages.\">Database Connectors</a>\n</li>\n</ul></td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Third-Party Integration <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15569e1_d15570e1_d15571e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fus1665702745424.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fus1665702745424.html\" title=\"The Uniface Universal Request Broker (URB) architecture allows you to deploy an application independently of architecture. It supports bidirectional, synchronous, and asynchronous communication between components. Components can access data in distributed databases and can be configured to run on any supported architecture.\">Universal Request Broker</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15572e1_d15573e1_d15574e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"juz1692183224178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/juz1692183224178.html\" title=\"The Uniface architecture enables you to integrate Uniface and non-Uniface components in a single application, and to deploy the application on a large variety of platforms and technologies.\">Integrating with Other Technologies</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15575e1_d15576e1_d15577e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"lyh1665702547569.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lyh1665702547569.html\" title=\"The Uniface SOAP connector handles call-out to web services. It translates Uniface activate statements into XML (based on data type mapping between Uniface and the web service XML schema), creates the SOAP envelope, sends the request, and receives and parses the reply.\">SOAP Connector</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ure1665702745274__li_d15578e1_d15579e1_d15580e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jsa1665702542990.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jsa1665702542990.html\" title=\"With the COM connector, Uniface can call out to COM objects and COM clients can call in to Uniface components. Neither side of the conversation needs to know the implementation details of the other side; COM objects appear to be Uniface services and the other way around. In addition, Uniface can call remote Uniface services through the COM connector.\">COM Connector</a>\n</li>\n</ul></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2532811\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Support for Distributed Applications Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 06, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface applications are normally distributed over networked computers, with components, data, and resources located and communicating with each other by means of various types of middleware. Content Overview The information in this collection describes the servers, connectors, and features that enable Uniface applications to be distributed over a network. Uniface Servers Uniface Application Middleware Uniface Server Uniface Router Network Support Network Support TCP Connector TLS Connector Asynchronous Messaging Asynchronous Messaging Message API Utility postmessage UTIMER Database Support DBMS Support Database Connectors Third-Party Integration Universal Request Broker Integrating with Other Technologies SOAP Connector COM Connector Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}